What Casting Directors Are Actually Looking For

Actors often think auditions are about impressing. Casting Directors are actually looking for clarity, professionalism, and trust.
Every audition silently answers three questions:
Can you do the role?
Can you take direction?
Can we work with you?
When you understand that, your auditions change completely.

Ich bin Operns√§ngerin (Sopran) mit langj√§hriger B√ºhnenerfahrung und Gesangslehrerin. Neben einem umfangreichen Opern-, Operetten- und Konzertrepertoire biete ich sowohl Gesangsunterricht als auch musikalische Beitr√§ge f√ºr festliche Anl√§sse und Galas an.

Gesangsunterricht:

Ich habe klassischen Gesang studiert und biete Online-Gesangsunterricht an, der individuell an Ihre M√∂glichkeiten, Interessen und Ziele angepasst ist ‚Äì in allen Stilrichtungen (Klassik, Musical, Pop, Rock). Mein Unterricht umfasst Einsing√ºbungen zur Entwicklung Ihrer Stimme, verbesserte Atmungstechniken und das Einstudieren von Liedern Ihrer Wahl. Dabei erkl√§re und demonstriere ich viel, um meinen Sch√ºlern die Inhalte verst√§ndlich zu machen. Der Unterricht findet bequem per Zoom oder WhatsApp statt. Gerne k√∂nnen Sie bei einem kostenlosen Kennenlernen meine Unterrichtsmethoden ausprobieren.

Musikalische Beitr√§ge f√ºr besondere Anl√§sse:

Ich bin auf der Suche nach neuen Wirkungsst√§tten und freue mich √ºber Solo- und gemeinsame Auftritte mit anderen K√ºnstlern. Ob Konzerte, Galas, Events oder festliche Anl√§sse ‚Äì ich biete Ihnen eine vielseitige, musikalisch hochwertige Gestaltung, die Ihre Veranstaltung zu einem unvergesslichen Erlebnis macht.

Melden Sie sich gerne bei mir, um einen Termin f√ºr den Gesangsunterricht oder die musikalische Gestaltung Ihrer Veranstaltung zu vereinbaren!

Viele Gr√º√üe
Amelia

items.text:
I wanted to share my gratitude for what was an outstanding holiday season of events, ranging from the local Midas Sign that kick things off this season  to the tree lighting ceremony at the Capitol in Sacramento.

Thank you to the University of California Student and Policy Center for the invitation to their well-stocked reception. The conversation was marvelous‚ÄîI haven't laughed that hard or had such deep conversations that left me wanting more in a long time. I also appreciate the Berkeley Policy Center for their intriguing night of discussion.

Finally, a shout-out to my friends at Sacramento Startup for the fun night at the Urban Hive. It is truly shaping up to be the place for events and gatherings, and I look forward to hosting an event there soon.

Start the new year learning, networking and making movies!.

Free introductory cinematography and direction workshop Saturday January 3rd, 2026. In Los Angeles

Complete this form for your free workshop https://forms.gle/hbAKhwT4jTsXzofXA

**Unlock Your Filmmaking Potential:**

‚Ä¢ Step onto a professional film set, gaining real-world experience while receiving guidance from seasoned instructors who are committed to your success. Be part of a film crew and make movies!

‚Ä¢ Immerse yourself in a vibrant and supportive community that empowers filmmakers to build connections and elevate their careers. Make friends for life.

‚Ä¢ Dive into hands-on workshops with cutting-edge digital cinema cameras and lighting equipment, bringing your creative vision to life like never before.

‚Ä¢ Gain exclusive access to our state-of-the-art studio, along with multiple stunning filming locations that will transform your projects into visual masterpieces.

‚Ä¢ Take advantage of free networking events featuring industry luminaries, where you‚Äôll have the chance to meet fellow filmmakers and gain invaluable insights.

‚Ä¢ Learn from industry veterans as they visit our studio, providing exclusive training sessions and mentorship opportunities that can shape your future in film.

‚Ä¢ Complete our intensive courses and earn a completion certificate that showcases your dedication and skills.

info@empoweringfilmmakers.org

**CASTING CALL!**

Dear Londoners,

*Eye to Eye* is currently casting a South Asian actress (playing age 50+) for the role of Pranjal.

Pranjal is known by her neighbours at best as a recluse, and at worst as ‚Äúcrazy.‚Äù She spends her days caring for a defunct robot in her living room, her own unique form of connection in an increasingly distant world.

Logline:
In an attempt to celebrate the return of her wife, an international aid worker, Kiara brings together a fractured community of neighbours to throw a party one that quickly spirals into chaos.

Shoot dates: Early February 2026 (7 days)
Production: 3rd-year UAL Film Students
Payment: Unpaid (travel expenses and food provided)

If you are interested, please send your reel to eyetoeye.film.ual@gmail.com.

We‚Äôre very excited to hear from you. Thank you so much!

‚ÄûDie Petrenkos ‚Äì Willkommen in Deutschland‚Äú

Gesucht wird eine Schauspielerin (18‚Äì22 Jahre),
blond oder br√ºnett, mit au√üergew√∂hnlich attraktiver Pr√§senz.

Wichtig sind:
sehr gutes Aussehen, klares Teenie-Schwarm-Potenzial, Sinnlichkeit, Selbstbewusstsein und eine selbstsichere, charismatische Spielhaltung.

Vom Typ her denken wir an eine moderne Ausstrahlung wie
Cameron Diaz in ‚ÄûVerr√ºckt nach Mary‚Äú oder
Megan Fox in ‚ÄûTransformers‚Äú.

Low-Budget-Kinofilm, Rolle ist bezahlt.

geplant f√ºr Juli und August 2026.

items.text:
Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver√§ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh√∂rt, Schauspiel nur √ºber Technik, Wissen und ‚Äûrichtig machen‚Äú zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet ‚Äì mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f√ºr Pr√§senz statt Performance. Wir haben w√∂chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie ‚Äûfertig‚Äú waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr√§senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment ‚Äì in 7 Buchstaben:

E ‚Äì Erleben

S ‚Äì Selbst

S ‚Äì Seele

E ‚Äì Emotion

N ‚Äì N√§he

Z ‚Äì Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

Wenn du den Link m√∂chtest, kommentiere **ESSENZ**.

Role: 
Astrya

Height: 5'6 (minimum)

Gender: Female
Ethnicity: White 
Accent:  Ideally Nordic or Neutral
Eye colour: Blue (or able to wear contact lenses)

- This is a physical role which requires a reasonably high level of fitness. 
- Weapons handling and combat experience is preferred. Though training will be provided. 
- A competent Norse /Neutral accent is essential.
- No visible tattoos is preferred. 
- Many of the filming locations will be rural. Own transport is Required.

To confirm your interest, Inbox your details.

Hi all, happy New Year! I hope this is okay to post here...I am a local actor and recent USC grad looking to update my reel footage, and I wanted to see if there are any other actors out there who would be interested in filming a scene together to use for your reel as well?

I've produced a handful of short films and web series in the past and will happily write a scene based on your character type and provide you with raw and edited footage. I'm hoping to film in the South Denver/Littleton/Centennial area in mid-January (but flexible!) Let me know if you're interested; the best way to get in touch is via email to aspenksomers@gmail.com. TIA!

items.text:
This is a question for all sag union people out there. Originally our feature film untethered we wanted make a sag film but after talking to my EP he recommended that we book a sag E actress and currently we are talking to on.

My question is under sag aftra rules what are the requirements for sag Eligible contracts, when it comes down to payment and per day?

topComments.text: Tyler Schacht in other words, if you hire a sag eligible actor, there are no contract rules for you to abide by. Only if they are Sag members already. Sag eligible means the actor has enough taft Hartley credits to apply to sag but have not applied yet...they are still nonunion. Whomever you hire, you can check to see if thry are sag or nonunion simply by calling the sag office and checking them thoroughly. The office can tell you, the casting director, if they are registered sag members or not.

Hi Tyler. SAG-AFTRA Actor and signatory producer here. You‚Äôre getting some incomplete answers. Basically it comes down to whether or not you decided to make your project under a SAG-AFTRA contract or not.  And pay requirements depend on the type of SAG-AFTRA contract you decided to use for your project. It has nothing to do with the union eligibility of one of the actors. 

Most of the people on this thread are correct about the SAG eligible Actor. SAG eligible means they are still non-union. They are eligible to join the union, but have not yet done so. So if your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA contract, they are still allowed to work your project, and there are no considerations you have to worry about in regard to the union. However, no SAG-AFTRA MEMBER actors may work on your nonunion project. 

This is where a lot of your answers are incomplete. If you did your project in a SAG-AFTRA contract, depending on the type of contract, you may or may not have to pay your actors at all. Even if they are SAG-AFTRA members. However, doing your project under a SAG contract will allow SAG-AFTRA members to act in your project. Contracts like SAG micro budget, SAG student, SAG Indie, and SAG ultra low budget all have ways of allowing for ultra low budget projects to do things like defer pay or no pay for actors. Even if they are full members of the union. But if you make your project a SAG-AFTRA contract project, then ALL actors in the project are covered and protected by SAG-AFTRA rules. This means that if you had budgeted a pay rate for actors, then all actors whether they are union members or not, would be subject to the same pay scale. Whether that is no pay, $150 a day, or $1000 a day. SAG-AFTRA contracts are not about treating some actors better than others. They are about making sure that all actors are protected, treated fairly, and paid fairly and most important transparently.

So if I am understanding correctly, you have a non-union project, that has employed a SAG-AFTRA eligible Actor. In this case, you have absolutely no requirements regarding the union. This is because your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA agreement.  the rules are about your project status. Not about the Actor‚Äôs eligibility status.

items.text:
*CALL FOR CROWD PARTICIPANTS (EXTRAS) // UNPAID*

*Berlin, SO36, 04.01.2026*

For our student short film project _Signal One_ we are looking for people to be part of the *background crowd* in a punk club scene, shot at *SO36 Berlin* around noon on *January 4th, 2026* .

What the movie is about: _After meeting face-to-face with the punk scene in 1977s West Berlin, a Yugoslav philosophy student has to learn how to confront and accept the person he really is._

We are looking for around 50 people who want to go wild in a *70s punk club scene* and are happy to dress accordingly. All ages and all genders welcome!

Unfortunately, the project is unpaid but we will provide snacks on set. Estimated shooting time: *approx. 3-4 hours* , starting around noon.

If you‚Äôre interested or want more information, feel free to text me by phone or send an email to signalone.casting@posteo.de. 

Looking forward to hearing from you :)

--- 

*German Version:*

F√ºr unser studentisches Kurzfilmprojekt Signal One suchen wir Leute, die *Teil der Crowd* (Kompars*innen) in einer *Punkclub-Szene* sein m√∂chten. Die Szene wird am 04.01.2026 gegen Mittag im *SO36 Berlin* gedreht.

Worum es im Film geht:

_Nachdem er der Punk-Szene im West-Berlin von 1977 begegnet ist, muss ein jugoslawischer Philosophiestudent lernen, sich seiner eigenen Identit√§t zu stellen und diese zu akzeptieren._

Wir suchen ca. 50 Personen, die Lust haben, in einer *70er-Punkclub-Szene* die Partyg√§ste zu spielen und sich passend zu kleiden. Alle Altersgruppen und Geschlechter willkommen!

Das Projekt ist unbezahlt, aber es wird Snacks am Set geben.

Gesch√§tzte Drehzeit: *ca. 3‚Äì4 Stunden* , ab Mittag.

Wenn du interessiert bist oder mehr Informationen haben m√∂chtest, melde dich gern direkt unter dieser Nummer oder E-Mail an signalone.casting@posteo.de

Wir freuen uns auf eure Nachrichten! :)

üé≠ CASTING CALL üé≠
Mr Poole (and The Father)
 in "Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde"
Grove Productions

We‚Äôre seeking an actor to join our touring production as Mr Poole, Dr Jekyll‚Äôs long-serving butler, who witnesses his master‚Äôs terrifying descent. This is a key supporting role with strong emotional scenes. The role also includes a small secondary part, The Father.

‚ú® Blind casting ‚Äì all actors welcome
üó£Ô∏è Working-class / regional accent required

üíº Pay
‚Ä¢ ¬£101 per performance (inc. holiday pay)
‚Ä¢ ¬£15 per hour for rehearsals (inc. holiday pay)

‚ö†Ô∏è Mid-run replacement ‚Äì fast learning essential
üé≠ Small rep company ‚Äì cast help move props/set & assist with get-outs
‚ôø Reasonable adjustments available

üìÖ Auditions: 9 January
üìÖ Rehearsals: 15 & 16 January

üéüÔ∏è Performance Dates:
‚Ä¢ 19 Jan ‚Äì Clevedon School (Bristol)
‚Ä¢ 3 Feb ‚Äì The Crypt (Gloucester)
‚Ä¢ 9/10 Feb (TBC) ‚Äì Hodge Hill (Birmingham)
‚Ä¢ 9 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 12 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 16 March ‚Äì Cheltenham Ladies‚Äô College

üì© To apply:
Send your CV + video audition (using the provided Poole extract) to
admin@groveproductions.org
Closing date for application: 5pm 6th January

Poole Extract

Context - Poole has become increasingly concerned about his master, Dr Jekyll, and has gone to Jekyll‚Äôs friend, Utterson, for help. In this scene, Poole has just asked Utterson to listen at the door to his master‚Äôs voice, as Poole believes it is not his master but a different man, or monster.

Poole:
Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But I‚Äôll do it yet. All this last week, he or it or whatever it is that lives in the laboratory, has been crying night and day for some sort of medicine and cannot get it to his mind. It was sometimes his way ‚Äì the master‚Äôs that is ‚Äì to write his orders on a sheet of paper and throw it on the stair. We‚Äôve had nothing else this week back. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking. Well sir, every day, ay, and twice and thrice in the same day, there have been orders and complaints, and I have been sent flying to all the wholesale chemists in town. Every time I brought the stuff back, there would be another paper telling me to return it, because it was not pure, and another order to a different firm. This drug is wanted bitter bad, sir, whatever for.

DM for more info

items.text:
Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver√§ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh√∂rt, Schauspiel nur √ºber Technik, Wissen und ‚Äûrichtig machen‚Äú zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet ‚Äì mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f√ºr Pr√§senz statt Performance. Wir haben w√∂chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie ‚Äûfertig‚Äú waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr√§senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment ‚Äì in 7 Buchstaben:

E ‚Äì Erleben

S ‚Äì Selbst

S ‚Äì Seele

E ‚Äì Emotion

N ‚Äì N√§he

Z ‚Äì Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

Wenn du den Link m√∂chtest, kommentiere **ESSENZ**.

Setgefl√ºster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl√ºster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur √ºber Drehtage, Abl√§ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern √ºber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. items.text:
Project: Bax P.I. Bite Size - Bax Meets Bonnie

Production company: ShoreHouse

Production type: Short/Mini Series

Role: Bonnie

Role type: lead (female, 20s-30s)

Project Rate: $200 flat rate (10 hrs. Single day shoot)

Union status: non union

Location: Monticello, FL

Key requirements: talent will be interacting with live animal (mini schnauzer)

For consideration, submit headshots to: hey@sammijay.com 

Key production dates:

Apply by Jan. 4; self-tapes due Jan. 7; decisions or call backs by Jan. 9. Wardrobe fitting Jan. 17; shoots Jan. 25 in Monticello, FL. Travel coverage does not include air travel, hiring for local and/or drivable only. We are open to shifting the shooting and fitting dates to work with talent availability.

About Bax P.I.: Imagine if Sin City and the Muppets had a baby‚Ä¶ that‚Äôs Bax P.I. It‚Äôs a world of mystery, crime, comedy, and friendship. When we‚Äôre in Baxter‚Äôs world, there‚Äôs very few human characters, one exception being Bonnie. When schnauzer detective Bax Dillinger meets the beautiful and mysterious Bonnie, we‚Äôre asked to question the reality of a small dog. To Bax, Bonnie is the most beautiful woman he‚Äôs ever seen, and in reality she‚Äôs his favorite chew bone.  This is part of a mini series to promote the feature length project set to go into production later in 2026.

Bonnie‚Äôs look: tall, slender physique. Minimum 5‚Äô 5‚Äù. Angular face. Extravagantly and elegantly fashioned. Red carpet level. Wears all white. Diversity encouraged.

Bonnie‚Äôs personality: mysterious, like she knows something we aren‚Äôt cool enough to know about. Edgy and witty. Intoxicatingly charming. A sophisticated flirt 

References: Carmen San Diego, Halle Berry, Debbie Harry, Uma Thurman

Levity Players Group, a professional theatre company performing in Independence, Kansas City, and other locations, is auditioning talented and dedicated actors.  Our next audition opportunity is:

Sunday, January 4th, 2026 ‚Äì 1:30 p.m.

Corinth Public Library

8100 Mission Road

Prairie Village, KS 66208

 

Please be there before 1:30 p.m., as the director has remarks to share with all auditioners.  The show we are auditioning for*** ***is*** The Canine Memorial Dinner Valentine‚Äôs Murder or Now, Youse Can‚Äôt Leave*****.*****  ***This show will be performed in February.  There is also the possibility of being cast in ***Miss Kitty Katty‚Äôs Cool Dude Ranch or Who Let the Horses Out of the Corral?****  That show will be performed in March.  There is also the possibility of being cast in ****Murder at the Real Estate Seminar or A Dead Seller Is a Motivated Seller.****  That show will be performed in April.*

In summary, this is an opportunity to secure three months of acting work by auditioning once.  We are definitely building a troupe; we are interested in working with dedicated actors who embody professional values. 

We present fully interactive, family-friendly murder mystery comedies.  Our covenant with our audiences and with our venue partners is that our shows will not contain objectionable language or situations.

Please bring headshots and resumes if you have them.  Auditions will consist of cold readings of sides.  No monologues will be needed.

This is absolutely a paid professional acting opportunity.  Pay is fifty dollars per show plus tips earned from serving guests dinner and drinks.  Tips have ranged from a low of approximately thirty dollars per show to a high of one hundred dollars per show.  In addition, the director may pay bonuses at the end of the run predicated upon an actor‚Äôs contribution to the team.  This is the number one paying professional theatre performance job in greater Kansas City on a dollar per hour invested basis.

We hope to meet you at the auditions.  If you have questions that need to be answered prior to the auditions, please feel free to telephone the company Artistic Director (Greg) at 314-456-3978

The Ghost That Could- Casting Call/Updates

Grateful the project was recently awarded the: @fromtheheartproductions ‚ÄòHot Film In The Making Roy W. Dean Grant FALL 2025‚Äô laurel

Excited to be moving into the test shoots stage of production in coming months(Jan-April). I went ahead and emailed some self tape request to those who expressed serious interest via email-

To anyone who responded before who is still interested in being part of the team/actor email: mattiemacaya@gmail.com with a resume and area of skill, attach resume

For self tapes please follow below instructions: 

For this stage, we would love to see a short, silent self-tape that gives us a sense of your emotional range and presence. No monologue is needed. 

Please submit this by NO LATER then end of dayJanuary 17 2026. For anyone interested in production assisting/marketing/makeup/etc email NO LATER then end of day January 20 2026.

What to include:

* Film either inside or outside ‚Äî whatever feels most comfortable and natural to you
* Keep the framing horizontal
* A simple moment where you move through an emotion or emotional shift (this can be very subtle)30seconds to 1 minute. 
* Please include a brief slate at the end with your name

After the slate, please answer the following two questions on camera (casually ‚Äî no need to overthink):

1. When do you feel most like yourself?
2. What‚Äôs something you notice about people that others often miss?

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Shoot Details: 

Test Shoot for Film Short

Non-union

Shoot Dates: TBD January - April 2026

Rate of Pay: Food/Beverage provided

Location: Denver, CO and surrounding locations

Side note from the üëª : if you‚Äôre submitting note the team will not respond to direct PMs on here nor will anyone chase you down for follow up if you are selected- that is ON YOU. Meet the self tape/application deadline if you‚Äòre serious and can commit, there can only be ONE ghost on this project everyone else will have to haunt elsewhere.

Thank you all for continued interest and support! Let‚Äôs collaborate on some magical storytelling in the new year and get this on 2026-2027 Festival Circuit.

Make your New Year‚Äôs resolution to start 2026 the right way: book your audition with the multi-award-winning drama academy proudly holding both the ùêåùêöùêßùêúùê°ùêûùê¨ùê≠ùêûùê´ & ùêçùê®ùê´ùê≠ùê° ùêñùêûùê¨ùê≠ ùêèùê´ùêûùê¨ùê≠ùê¢ùê†ùêû ùêÄùê∞ùêöùê´ùêù ùêüùê®ùê´ ùêÅùêûùê¨ùê≠ ùêÉùê´ùêöùê¶ùêö ùêíùêúùê°ùê®ùê®ùê• ùê®ùêü ùê≠ùê°ùêû ùêòùêûùêöùê´ ùüêùüéùüêùüì/ùüêùüî and the ùêÑùüê ùêåùêûùêùùê¢ùêö ùêÄùê∞ùêöùê´ùêù ùêüùê®ùê´ ùêÅùêûùê¨ùê≠ ùêÉùê´ùêöùê¶ùêö ùêíùêúùê°ùê®ùê®ùê• ùê®ùêü ùê≠ùê°ùêû ùêòùêûùêöùê´ ùüêùüéùüêùüì/ùüêùüî, as well as being a ùêîùêä ùêíùê¶ùêöùê•ùê• ùêÅùêÆùê¨ùê¢ùêßùêûùê¨ùê¨ ùêÄùê∞ùêöùê´ùêùùê¨ ùüêùüéùüêùüì finalist, representing Manchester in the ùêÅùêûùê¨ùê≠ ùêíùê¶ùêöùê•ùê• ùêÅùêÆùê¨ùê¢ùêßùêûùê¨ùê¨ category‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ùêåùêöùê´ùêõùê•ùêû ùêÄùêúùêöùêùùêûùê¶ùê≤ ùê¢ùêß ùêíùê∞ùê¢ùêßùê≠ùê®ùêß, ùêåùêöùêßùêúùê°ùêûùê¨ùê≠ùêûùê´.

 

We‚Äôre also recognised by ùêíùê©ùê®ùê≠ùê•ùê¢ùê†ùê°ùê≠, the UK‚Äôs leading casting platform, for our professional standard of training.

 

So, why not commit to the training that will turn you from ‚Äúsomeone who acts‚Äù into an actor who succeeds?

 

We don‚Äôt just run drama classes ‚Äì we train serious, committed actors for real careers in film, TV and theatre.

_________________________________________

 

ùêìùê´ùêöùê¢ùêßùê¢ùêßùê† ùêìùê°ùêöùê≠ ùêÄùêúùê≠ùêÆùêöùê•ùê•ùê≤ ùêÅùêÆùê¢ùê•ùêùùê¨ ùêÇùêöùê´ùêûùêûùê´ùê¨:

 

With weekly classes at Marble Academy, you will train under award-winning tutor Christian Le Feuvre, focusing on several modules including:

‚Ä¢ ùêíùêúùê´ùê¢ùê©ùê≠ & ùê¨ùêúùêûùêßùêû ùê∞ùê®ùê´ùê§ ‚Äì breaking down text like a pro

‚Ä¢ ùêÄùêÆùêùùê¢ùê≠ùê¢ùê®ùêß ùê≠ùêûùêúùê°ùêßùê¢ùê™ùêÆùêû ‚Äì self-tapes and in-room auditions that stand out

‚Ä¢ ùêÇùê°ùêöùê´ùêöùêúùê≠ùêûùê´ & ùêûùê¶ùê®ùê≠ùê¢ùê®ùêß ‚Äì truthful, layered performances

‚Ä¢ ùêéùêß-ùêúùêöùê¶ùêûùê´ùêö ùê¨ùê§ùê¢ùê•ùê•ùê¨ ‚Äì marks, continuity and confidence

‚Ä¢ ùêèùê´ùê®ùêüùêûùê¨ùê¨ùê¢ùê®ùêßùêöùê• ùê¶ùê¢ùêßùêùùê¨ùêûùê≠‚Äì how real actors work, prepare and behave.

 

You‚Äôll not only improve the talent you already have ‚Äì you‚Äôll unlearn bad habits, stop doing the things that hold so many actors back, and replace them with sharp, reliable technique.

 

Whether you‚Äôre just starting or ready to level up, this is where you turn ‚ÄúI‚Äôd love to act‚Äù into ‚ÄúI‚Äôm building a real career.‚Äù

_______________________________________________________

 

ùêåùê®ùê´ùêû ùêìùê°ùêöùêß ùêö ùêÇùê•ùêöùê¨ùê¨: ùêÄ ùêÇùê´ùêûùêöùê≠ùê¢ùêØùêû ùêáùêÆùêõ:

 

That‚Äôs not all‚ÄîMarble Academy produce award-winning films, hosts interactive workshops, extremely popular networking events for actors and filmmakers, and provides invaluable casting opportunities for our students. We take immense pride in the accomplishments of our graduates, many of whom have gone on to star in acclaimed projects.

______________________________________________________

 

ùêÄùêÆùêùùê¢ùê≠ùê¢ùê®ùêß & ùêÑùêßùê´ùê®ùê• ùêüùê®ùê´ ùüêùüéùüêùüî:

 

If you‚Äôre ready to take your craft seriously:

1. Visit www.marbleacademy.co.uk

2. Check out all the information and read our reviews

3. Apply for an audition and make 2026 the year you stop ‚Äúthinking about it‚Äù and actually do something for your future as an actor.

___________________________________________________

 

ùêÉùêéùêç‚Äôùêì ùêÅùêÑ ùêÄùêç ùêÄùêÇùêìùêéùêë ùêÅùêÑùêÇùêÄùêîùêíùêÑ ùêòùêéùêî ùêñùêÄùêçùêì ùêìùêé; ùêÅùêÑ ùêÄùêç ùêÄùêÇùêìùêéùêë ùêÅùêÑùêÇùêÄùêîùêíùêÑ ùêòùêéùêî ùêáùêÄùêïùêÑ ùêìùêé.

items.text:
Hi everyone. This is future-facing, not an immediate ask.

I‚Äôm a director developing my first feature. My first completed screenplay turned out to be the kind of project that, if I‚Äôm fortunate, may represent a culmination rather than a starting point, so I‚Äôm thinking long term and realistically.

The project is an independent, non-studio film. It is a deportation story set in Honduras and designed to be roughly three hours. I‚Äôm fully aware this is not industry friendly or something a studio would buy, and that is intentional. This is a passion project I expect to finance independently if it ever happens.

I‚Äôm not looking for script feedback.

What I‚Äôm trying to do is educate myself years in advance.

For those of you who have worked on or around independent features, especially international or location-heavy productions, I would appreciate insight on practical difficulties you encountered, mistakes you wish you had planned for earlier, insurance or legal considerations I should be aware of, and logistical challenges that often get underestimated.

I am actively working on smaller and more practical projects to build toward this, but I want to understand the realities ahead of time so I‚Äôm not na√Øve about what it takes.

Any experience-based advice is appreciated. Thank you for reading.

For those of you who have worked on or around independent features, especially international or location-heavy productions, I would appreciate insight on practical difficulties you encountered, mistakes you wish you had planned for earlier, insurance or legal considerations I should be aware of, and logistical challenges that often get underestimated.

I am actively working on smaller and more practical projects to build toward this, but I want to understand the realities ahead of time so I‚Äôm not na√Øve about what it takes.

Any experience-based advice is appreciated. Thank you for reading.

# In search of short scripts and BTS videos.

Happy new year creatives! I wanted to hit the ground running with a couple requests.

Short scripts: My creative partner and I are reading short film scripts to be produced this year. We're specifically looking for under 15 pages, ideally written in a way that they can be produced locally. Open to most genres, but we're drawn to scripts that feel fresh, thought-provoking, and bring something new to the table. We're aiming to produce at least three short films created by our passionate and committed community of filmmakers. We also want to encourage script writers who are open to having their work directed by others‚Äîcollaboration is at the heart of what we‚Äôre building. If you have something you‚Äôre excited about, please send your scripts to my partner Ben! [benjaminhorvat.media@gmail.com](mailto:benjaminhorvat.media@gmail.com). Thank you.

BTS video: I‚Äôve had a fun little project on the back burner for months now, and it occurred to me what would bring it all together is BTS video footage from local Bay Area filmmakers. If you have some that you would like to contribute, or you'd like to learn more about the project, email me.

Other outlets I offer for artists:

Discord server

Newsletter

Actor database/casting service

Crew recommendation list

Filmmaking workshops (in development)

Most of this is geared towards SF Bay Area filmmakers and actors, but not exclusively.

If you‚Äôd like details on any of these, please shoot me an email!

[Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com](mailto:Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com)

‚ú® Still time to join us at the CAL-Western NATS Conference! ‚ú®

I‚Äôm excited to share that I‚Äôll be teaching a BeSingGargle¬© workshop at the upcoming CAL-Western Region Conference of the National Association of Teachers of Singing, taking place January 16‚Äì18, 2026 (MLK Weekend) at San Jos√© State University.
https://www.calwestnats.org/reg-conference

This regional conference brings together NATS teachers and students from Arizona, California, Hawai‚Äòi, Nevada, and Utah, and I‚Äôm honored to be participating as:
üé§ A workshop presenter
üéº A judge
üåü A proud teacher with two students advancing to the semifinals

üé∂ About the BeSingGargle¬© Workshop

BeSingGargle¬© is a playful, water-based vocal warm-up designed to help singers:

 ‚Ä¢ Open range and smooth register transitions
 ‚Ä¢ Breathe with more ease and clarity
 ‚Ä¢ Shape vowels and consonants with greater freedom
 ‚Ä¢ Quickly and naturally clear phlegm while lightly lubricating the voice
 ‚Ä¢ Calm nerves and boost confidence through gentle vagal and sensory activation

A special bonus: BeSingGargle¬© works beautifully online, making it a powerful and engaging tool for virtual voice lessons as well as in-person teaching.

The session will include a live demonstration, a student demo, and hands-on participation. It‚Äôs joyful, grounding, and surprisingly effective, helping singers move out of their heads, into their bodies, and onto the stage with confidence and ease. 

‚è∞ Late registration is still open!

If you‚Äôd like to attend the conference and join this workshop, you can sign up here:

üëâ Late Registration Form:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd6zm-XCK_3FYN4qZSLzsTSoV7pH5zXuL-yXW9LvW5NU_aJwA/viewform

I‚Äôd love to see fellow teachers, singers, and students there for a weekend of learning, connection, and inspired singing. üé∂‚ú®

2025 NATS Cal-Western Region Conference Registration

**Casting Call for a 20-min short**

Hi everyone! We‚Äôre looking for non-union actors who are based on Vancouver, BC. We're thrilled to have new blood in our team!

**Production Information:**

-Location: Vancouver, BC

-Shoot Dates: Feb 21st-22nd.

-Genre:Drama, Thriller

-Non-Union/Volunteer

-Crafty+IMDb credit provided

**Roles:**

**Officer Shaw Male 28-50**

A true believer in justice and law enforcement. He doesn‚Äôt believe mentalism is anything more than cheap party tricks, but he finds Chaz and his shtick entertaining, so he allows Chaz to perform for him and explain himself. With every word Chaz says in his defence, Officer Shaw starts to see through Chaz‚Äôs persona and eventually confronts him about the moral, ethical and legal complications his profession entails. The conversation reaches a boiling point when Chaz attempts to read Officer Shaw‚Äôs mind by repeating the last words spoken to Shaw from his missing daughter.

**To submit:**

Please submit headshot and demo reel to **theartofreadingminds.short@gmail.com** and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

**AUDITION NOTICE** -- LOVE, LOSS AND WHAT I WORE

Authors: Nora Ephron and Delia Ephron (based on the book by Ilene Beckerman)
Director: Olivia Etey
Producer: Janet Ellis
Audition Date/Time: Tuesday, January 6, 7 PM
Location: Peninsula Productions (14600 North Bluff Road, White Rock)

Preparation: Please prepare two short 1-2 minute monologues. One comedic and one dramatic.
Play Summary:

Love, Loss, and What I Wore uses a series of monologues and ensemble vignettes to explore the
female experience through the lens of fashion. By using clothing as a "time capsule," the play
recounts pivotal life moments‚Äîmarriages, heartbreaks, and family dynamics‚Äîall triggered by
memories of specific garments. From the universal struggle of bra shopping to poignant stories of
resilience and grief, the production highlights how a woman‚Äôs wardrobe serves as a roadmap of her
identity and history.

Characters:
The play features a diverse ensemble of 5‚Äì7 women ages 40+. Except for Gingy, all actors portray
multiple characters.

Gingy: The central narrator and anchor of the play. She is wise and self-deprecating,
recounting her life story from childhood through several marriages and milestones.
Ensemble A (The Matriarch/Dramatist): Primarily portrays mother figures and women
navigating deep loss or family traditions.
Ensemble B (The Comedian): Handles high-energy, humorous rants regarding fashion
frustrations, such as the "I Hate My Purse" monologue.
Ensemble C (The Survivor): Focuses on characters navigating life‚Äôs hardships, including stories
of illness, aging, and reclaiming personal power.
Ensemble D (The Ingenue/Rebel): Portrays younger characters dealing with first loves,
wedding dress shopping, and finding their identity through style.

This staged reading will be at Peninsula Studio Theatre from March 5, 6, 7, 8, 2026. Rehearsals will
be in January - March 2026. Actors are paid an honourarium and get free parking.

If you would like to audition, please send your headshot and resume to
janet@peninsulaproductions.org 

We look forward to hearing from you!

 #peninsulaproductions #arts #culture #theatre #stage #supporthearts #surreybc #auditions #actors
